<item>
            <title>[CLI-138] No &apos;--&apos; option for terminating options processing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CLI-138</link>
                <project id="12310463" key="CLI">Commons CLI</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears that neither 1.0 not 1.1 have a &apos;-&lt;del&gt;&apos; option as the &apos;end processing options&apos; option.  This is immensely useful to allow parameter that are not options that start with a hyphen.  grep for example does this.  I think it is a bug rather than an enhancement request, I think Commons CLI should support &apos;&lt;/del&gt;-&apos; option.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Ubuntu 7.04 Feisty Fawn&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
        <key id="12374564">CLI-138</key>
            <summary>No &apos;--&apos; option for terminating options processing</summary>
